OL,3,CUS and Israel accused of overselling
OL,4,Cmilitary success in Iran
OL,6,FReductions in Iran's missile attacks
OL,7,Fhave been cited as evidence of the
OL,8,Fdestruction of their capabilities, but
OL,9,Fsources believe this is also
OL,10,Freflective of Iran preparing for the
OL,11,Flong game.
OL,13,FA British intelligence source added:
OL,14,F"The IRGC have spent decades
OL,15,Forganising themselves to resist
OL,16,Finsurgency and survive internal and
OL,17,Fexternal attacks. All this is now
OL,18,Fcoming into play. Their drone and
OL,19,Fmissile armament, built over decades,
OL,20,Fmeans they can asymmetrically erode
OL,21,Fconventional armies and navies."
OL,26,@vD@AOU}D@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
